      "type": "Claim",
      "name": "CFD model predicts absolute hemolysis index within acceptable uncertainty bounds for Class III VAD operating envelope",
      "description": "The CFD hemolysis model, applied to the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry across 5 flow-speed operating points, produces normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) predictions that remain below the absolute clinical threshold of 0.1 g/100 L across all Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification samples. Mesh sensitivity studies, turbulence model selection rationale, and scalar transport verification support the plausibility of the prediction. The claim scope is restricted to the operating envelope defined in COU2 (2–6 L/min, 2000–3600 RPM) and does not extend to off-design transient conditions.",
      "claimScope": "Operating envelope: 2–6 L/min, 2000–3600 RPM; FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry; steady-state RANS with power-law hemolysis scalar transport",
      "claimStatement": "NIH predictions are below 0.1 g/100 L with 95th-percentile Monte Carlo confidence across all 5 COU2 operating points"
    },
