      "acceptanceCriteria": "GCI < 5% for NIH QoI on fine mesh; Richardson extrapolation applied; three mesh levels documented.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement completed; GCI for NIH = 4.2% on fine mesh (14.3M cells), meeting the 5% threshold. However, near-wall y+ consistency across operating points not fully documented for all 5 conditions. Achieved level 3 due to incomplete y+ reporting."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions match COU2 operating points within ±2%; fluid temperature and viscosity controlled and documented.",
      "rationale": "Experimental flow rates controlled within ±1.5% of target. Rotational speed maintained within ±0.8%. Fluid temperature variation ±1.2°C across runs introduces viscosity uncertainty of approximately ±3%, slightly exceeding the ±2% criterion for level 4. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., MARE) defined a priori; validation against experimental NIH at all 5 operating points; uncertainty in experimental measurements propagated.",
      "rationale": "MARE of 12.3% computed across 5 operating points. Experimental uncertainty (CV < 8%) propagated using standard error propagation. However, comparison metric acceptance threshold was defined post-hoc after observing results rather than a priori, reducing confidence in objectivity. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (NIH) directly maps to clinical hemolysis endpoint; scalar transport model captures dominant hemolysis mechanisms for the operating regime.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the primary regulatory hemolysis metric and directly maps to clinical consequence. Power-law hemolysis model captures shear-induced hemolysis but does not capture contact hemolysis or recirculation zone contributions at low flow rates. Relevance is high for mid-range operating points but reduced at 2 L/min. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments performed on same pump geometry, same fluid, same operating conditions as COU2; no surrogate geometry substitution.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry matching COU2. However, experiments used bovine blood while COU2 application involves human blood analog. Viscosity correction applied but species-specific RBC fragility differences not characterized. Surrogate fluid reduces validation relevance to level 2 for MRL 5 requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence criteria documented; residual monitoring for all transport equations; round-off error assessment for double precision arithmetic.",
      "rationale": "Convergence residuals reported (10^-5 for continuity, 10^-6 for momentum) but iterative convergence of hemolysis scalar transport equation not separately monitored. Round-off error assessment not performed. Factor flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5; achieved level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent review of simulation setup; documented checklist for boundary condition application; peer verification of UDF implementation.",
      "rationale": "No independent peer review of simulation setup or UDF implementation performed. Single analyst responsible for model setup and post-processing without cross-check. Use error factor not assessed; epistemic gap identified. Achieved level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified against experimental data; hemolysis constitutive model uncertainty quantified; alternative model forms evaluated.",
      "rationale": "k-omega SST selected based on literature precedent for rotating machinery but not validated against LDA measurements for this specific pump geometry. Power-law hemolysis model coefficients (C=1.8e-6, alpha=0.765, beta=2.416) taken from Giersiepen et al. without re-calibration. Model form uncertainty not quantified. Achieved level 1; major epistemic gap."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All boundary condition inputs characterized with uncertainty distributions; inlet velocity profiles measured or justified; fluid properties documented with temperature dependence.",
      "rationale": "Inlet flow rate and rotational speed specified with uncertainty bounds derived from pump operating specifications. Fluid viscosity temperature dependence modeled using Newtonian approximation. Inlet velocity profile assumed uniform (turbulent pipe flow) without direct measurement — a simplification that may introduce error at low flow rates. Achieved level 2."
    },
