    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment package for COU2 VAD hemolysis prediction is accepted for regulatory submission purposes. ValidationResults demonstrate NIH predictions within 12.3% MARE of experimental data, with Monte Carlo 95th-percentile NIH (0.087 g/100 L) below the clinical threshold (0.1 g/100 L). Seven of thirteen credibility factors have been assessed; six remain as documented epistemic gaps consistent with the preliminary assessment stage. The Claim node (https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-credibility-claim) summarizes the overall credibility position. Full closure of epistemic gaps required prior to final regulatory submission.",
